unhindered
access to Aleppo, so that
monitors can watch

12:52.005 --> 12:56.442 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
those trying to flee that
war-ravaged city.

12:56.476 --> 13:02.649 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was a welcome sight for
thousands of Syrians
trapped in Eastern Aleppo,
waiting in the

13:02.682 --> 13:04.517 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
cold.

13:04.550 --> 13:09.489 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Evacuations resumed overnight,
after days
of delays, under terms of a
fragile cease-fire.

13:09.522 --> 13:13.092 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAN (through translator): We
were very hungry.

13:13.126 --> 13:15.228 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
God will take revenge on our
behalf.

13:15.261 --> 13:18.364 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Hopefully, we will return to
Aleppo.

13:18.398 --> 13:23.569 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Forty-seven
children trapped
in an orphanage were among those
rescued,

13:23.603 --> 13:29.509 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but the U.N. children's agency,
UNICEF, reported
some were in critical condition.

13:29.542 --> 13:35.515 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The evacuees were being ferried
to Idlib province,
widely expected to be the next
front in the

13:35.548 --> 13:37.316 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
government's offensive.

13:37.350 --> 13:43.856 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
At the same time, buses
evacuated civilians
from two Shiite villages in
Idlib besieged

13:43.890 --> 13:45.725 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
by rebels.

13:45.758 --> 13:51.798 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Syrian army and its allies
demanded that
evacuation in exchange for
letting thousands

13:51.831 --> 13:56.969 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
