incident in Berlin with the
truck driving
into a crowd in a Christmas
market.

31:25.984 --> 31:30.055 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There was also a shooting at an
Islamic mosque
today in Zurich, Switzerland.

31:30.088 --> 31:35.227 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But he's saying these are -- I'm
quoting now
from his statement.

31:35.260 --> 31:39.765 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He condemned the Berlin attack,
said: "The
Islamic State and other Islamist
terrorists

31:39.798 --> 31:42.434 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are slaughtering Christians as
part of their
global jihad."

31:42.467 --> 31:47.472 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he said the U.S. -- he said
civilized
world must change its thinking.

31:47.506 --> 31:51.843 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We don't have clear evidence yet
of what was
behind these attacks.

31:51.877 --> 31:58.216 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's assuming that it's all an
Islamic -- or
an Islamist motive here.

31:58.250 --> 32:01.953 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TAMARA KEITH: And the civilized
world line
came in a tweet.

32:01.987 --> 32:03.088 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
This is not new.

32:03.121 --> 32:06.525 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What is new is that Donald Trump
is now president-elect.

32:06.558 --> 32:13.999 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Donald Trump turning to Twitter
to declare
that something is Islamist
terrorism before

32:14.032 --> 32:17.903 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the broader security community,
before the
White House, before others have
been willing

32:17.936 --> 32:21.706 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
to declare that, before
investigators have
been willing to declare that,
that is not

32:21.740 --> 32:22.707 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
new.

32:22.741 --> 32:24.109 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He's done that before in past
instance.

32:24.142 --> 32:27.245 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We saw that
during the campaign,
Amy.

32:27.279 --> 32:30.215 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Do we expect that this is just
going to continue
when he's president?

32:30.248 --> 32:31.950 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
AMY WALTER: Absolutely.

32:31.983 --> 32:36.822 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then the question becomes,
what do we
do about it once he's in office
and hear,

32:36.855 --> 32:41.226 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of course, the broader dialogue
from him and
the people around him?

32:41.259 --> 32:46.131 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, we are --
as we have
known about these, we have been
waiting ourselves

32:46.164 --> 32:51.369 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to decide or to know what
exactly we can say,
because the German authorities,
the Turkish

32:51.403 --> 32:54.139 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
authorities were only putting
out so much
information.

32:54.172 --> 32:58.009 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it appears that Donald Trump
has already
drawn these conclusions, and so
we report

32:58.043 --> 32:59.010 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
them.

32:59.044 --> 33:00.011 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Amy Walter, Tamara Keith, thank
you both.

33:00.045 --> 33:01.012 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
TAMARA KEITH: You're welcome.

33:01.046 --> 33:09.788 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
AMY WALTER: Thank you, Judy.

33:09.821 --> 33:20.799 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Next: Of the
stains left on
our national heritage by the
country's history

33:20.832 --> 33:27.505 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
of slavery and Jim Crow
segregation, perhaps
the least discussed is the
practice of racial

33:27.539 --> 33:32.944 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
lynchings, executions of
African-Americans
done outside the judicial system
and often

33:32.978 --> 33:37.282 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
intended to subdue black
communities into
passivity.

33:37.315 --> 33:42.287 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Hari Sreenivasan looks at a plan
to help bring
that conversation to the fore.

33:42.320 --> 33:46.625 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The plan is to
commemorate
victims of racially motivated
lynchings with

33:46.658 --> 33:48.727 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a memorial in Montgomery,
Alabama.

33:48.760 --> 33:52.964 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The design calls for some 800
columns, which,
upon closer viewing, reveal
themselves to

33:52.998 --> 33:56.835 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
be suspended from above in a way
that mimics
a hanging.

33:56.868 --> 34:01.206 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Each will bear the names of
lynching victims,
over 4,000 in all, as well as
the date and

34:01.239 --> 34:03.275 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
location of their deaths.

34:03.308 --> 34:07.646 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A companion courtyard will hold
duplicate
columns which will be moved to
the county

34:07.679 --> 34:12.117 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
of the lynchings each
commemorates, once that
local community accepts it.

34:12.150 --> 34:15.787 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A recent $10 million donation
from sibling
philanthropists Pat and Jon
Stryker brings

34:15.820 --> 34:18.924 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the project closer to its
planned 2018 opening.

34:18.957 --> 34:23.361 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For more on all this, we turn to
Bryan Stevenson,
the founder of the Equal Justice
Initiative,

34:23.395 --> 34:26.431 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
which created the concept and is
overseeing
its completion.

34:26.464 --> 34:27.933 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Bryan, thanks for being with us.

34:27.966 --> 34:30.402 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
First, why do we need a memorial
like this?

34:30.435 --> 34:33.939 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BRYAN STEVENSON, Founder, Equal
Justice Initiative:
Well, I think we're still
haunted by our history

34:33.972 --> 34:35.607 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of racial inequality.

34:35.640 --> 34:39.077 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We are really burdened by this
legacy.

34:39.110 --> 34:41.980 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I don't think we have
acknowledged it
adequately.

34:42.013 --> 34:46.484 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We terrorized African-Americans
at the end
of the 19th century and through
half of the

34:46.518 --> 34:48.219 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
20th century.

34:48.253 --> 34:52.624 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The demographic geography of
this country
was shaped by this era of racial
terror and

34:52.657 --> 34:54.426 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
lynching.

34:54.459 --> 34:56.494 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The black people who went to
Cleveland and
Chicago and Detroit went there
as refugees

34:56.528 --> 34:58.096 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and exiles from terror.

34:58.129 --> 34:59.764 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And we haven't owned up to it.

34:59.798 --> 35:01.132 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And I think we need to.

35:01.166 --> 35:04.936 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It took us 15 years to build a
9/11 memorial
here in New York.

35:04.970 --> 35:06.571 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And I think that's important.

35:06.604 --> 35:10.709 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I think it's critically
necessary that we
remember what happened on that
day.

35:10.742 --> 35:15.780 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it's equally important that
we acknowledge
this history of terror that I
think still

35:15.814 --> 35:21.086 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
undermines our ability to be
free, to be just
with one another, to kind of
shake the burden

35:21.119 --> 35:25.423 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of racial inequality that still
undermines
us in many areas.

35:25.457 --> 35:28.793 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: This is part
of a longer
project that you have been
working on.

35:28.827 --> 35:32.464 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You documented, I think, 8,000
lynchings over
almost a 75-year period.

35:32.497 --> 35:36.001 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You even grabbed jars of soil
from each of
these sites.

35:36.034 --> 35:37.869 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Why?

35:37.902 --> 35:40.805 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BRYAN STEVENSON: The American
South is littered
with the iconography of the
Confederacy.

35:40.839 --> 35:46.144 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And there are communities where
the devastation
of slavery, where the
devastation of the genocide

35:46.177 --> 35:51.216 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of Native people has not been
acknowledged,
has not been recognized.

35:51.249 --> 35:55.186 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Lynchings provide an opportunity
for us to
go to very specific places.

35:55.220 --> 36:01.059 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Many of these acts of terror
took place on
courthouse lawns, in front of
schools, in

36:01.092 --> 36:04.396 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
front of churches, in front of
places that
still exist today.

36:04.429 --> 36:09.367 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, we have been asking people
in the community
to engage in acts of
truth-telling and acts

36:09.401 --> 36:12.537 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of recovery, reconciliation,
reparation.

36:12.570 --> 36:15.206 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think we need that in this
country.

36:15.240 --> 36:16.608 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In South Africa, you have seen
that.

36:16.641 --> 36:17.809 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
In Rwanda, you have seen that.

36:17.842 --> 36:19.711 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
In Germany, you have seen that.

36:19.744 --> 36:23.948 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think they are healthier
communities because
they acknowledge their histories
of mass atrocity

36:23.982 --> 36:25.784 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and violence.

36:25.817 --> 36:29.254 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think we're less healthy
because we haven't
talked about the genocide of
Native people,

36:29.287 --> 36:32.057 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we haven't talked about slavery,
we haven't
talked about lynching.

36:32.090 --> 36:34.526 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think, to get there, we're
going to
have to do these tasks.

36:34.559 --> 36:37.228 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We're going to have to take
these steps.

36:37.262 --> 36:40.465 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the community involvement,
the soil collections
are part of that process.

36:40.498 --> 36:44.669 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The countries
you mentioned,
they didn't get there very
quickly.

36:44.702 --> 36:46.471 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
There was resistance.

36:46.504 --> 36:48.773 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Is there resistance, especially
in the South
in the United States, when you
bring up the

36:48.807 --> 36:50.108 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
idea of this memorial?

36:50.141 --> 36:53.545 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRYAN STEVENSON: I think there
is certainly
a reluctance.

36:53.578 --> 36:55.447 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We have denied this history for
a long time.

36:55.480 --> 36:58.349 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think we have become such a
punitive society.

36:58.383 --> 37:00.251 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have the highest rate of
incarceration
in the world.

37:00.285 --> 37:04.656 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think a lot of people are
afraid to talk
about slavery, are afraid to
talk about lynching

37:04.689 --> 37:08.093 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and segregation because they
fear they will
be punished.

37:08.126 --> 37:11.463 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We don't have an interest in
punishing America
for this history, but we don't
believe we

37:11.496 --> 37:14.799 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
can be free until we acknowledge
this history.

37:14.833 --> 37:20.105 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Issues of police violence,
issues of discrimination,
issues of lack of diversity are
rooted in

37:20.138 --> 37:24.109 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
an absence of truth-telling
about our history.

37:24.142 --> 37:29.781 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so we have to just persuade
people that
there is something powerful and
positive and

37:29.814 --> 37:34.119 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
beautiful that can come when we
acknowledge
these histories, however
painful, and make

37:34.152 --> 37:36.020 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
our ways forward.

37:36.054 --> 37:40.959 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Germany is a nation that we
trust more today
because they don't have these --
they don't

37:40.992 --> 37:42.393 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
have statutes to Adolf Hitler.

37:42.427 --> 37:44.896 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They don't celebrate the Nazis.

37:44.929 --> 37:48.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Rwanda is a healthier place
because they have
acknowledged that legacy.

37:48.399 --> 37:49.801 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So is South America.

37:49.834 --> 37:52.137 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think America has to replicate
that if we're
going to really be free.

37:52.170 --> 37:56.107 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: I tried to
give a group
description of what it looks
like or what

37:56.141 --> 37:59.811 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it will look like, but what are
you hoping
that people take away if they
walk through

37:59.844 --> 38:01.546 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and visit the space?

38:01.579 --> 38:06.017 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BRYAN STEVENSON: I hope people
will begin
to think differently about who
we are and

38:06.050 --> 38:07.852 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
what our past is.

38:07.886 --> 38:11.923 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You know, this donation comes
from Jon and
Pat Stryker, who are honoring
their father,

38:11.956 --> 38:15.360 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who stood for civil rights, who
understood
the importance of civil rights.

38:15.393 --> 38:17.762 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I think we have to create
spaces.

38:17.795 --> 38:20.098 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Holocaust memorials are very
powerful
places.

38:20.131 --> 38:24.369 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You walk through them, you
understand things,
you come out and you say never
again.

38:24.402 --> 38:28.139 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think we need to create
spaces in America
where we begin to confront this
history of

38:28.173 --> 38:32.177 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
racial inequality and we walk
out and we say
never again.

38:32.210 --> 38:34.112 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We want them to be sober places.

38:34.145 --> 38:38.783 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We want them to be informational
places, but
we also want them to be places
where there's

38:38.816 --> 38:42.654 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
beauty, where there's hope,
where there's
the chance for transformation.

38:42.687 --> 38:44.522 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And I think we can do that.

38:44.556 --> 38:49.661 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But we can't do it without
spending more time
creating the kind of cultural
infrastructure

38:49.694 --> 38:51.996 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that I hope this memorial will
contribute
to.

38:52.030 --> 38:58.870 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Is there a
through-line
or a legacy of lynching in the
criminal justice

38:58.903 --> 38:59.871 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
system today?

38:59.904 --> 39:01.773 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
BRYAN STEVENSON: Oh, absolutely.

39:01.806 --> 39:06.177 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, you know, at the end of
the Civil
War, we didn't really deal with
the great

39:06.211 --> 39:08.112 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
evil of American slavery.

39:08.146 --> 39:11.649 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The great evil of American
slavery was an
involuntary servitude of forced
labor.

39:11.683 --> 39:15.987 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I believe the great evil of
American slavery
was the narrative of racial
difference that

39:16.020 --> 39:18.489 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
we created to legitimate it.

39:18.523 --> 39:21.726 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And because we didn't address
that in the
13th Amendment, I don't think
slavery ended.

39:21.759 --> 39:23.895 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I think it just evolved.

39:23.928 --> 39:27.832 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And what we did in this country
is, we began
to criminalize black people.

39:27.865 --> 39:33.438 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the late 19th century,
convict leasing
was a new kind of slavery, where
we put black

39:33.471 --> 39:37.875 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
people in jails and prisons, and
then leased
them to do the same work they
would have done

39:37.909 --> 39:39.744 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
as enslaved people.

39:39.777 --> 39:45.016 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And that narrative of
criminality was very
much behind lynching, even
though black people

39:45.049 --> 39:49.887 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
were being lynched for things
like not using
the colored entrance, for asking
for better

39:49.921 --> 39:51.990 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
wages, for scolding white
children.

39:52.023 --> 39:55.593 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Elizabeth Lawrence was lynched
in Birmingham,
Alabama, because she told white
kids to stop

39:55.627 --> 39:57.328 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
throwing stones at her.

39:57.362 --> 40:02.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And even though these acts were
not crimes,
they challenged this racial
hierarchy.

40:02.233 --> 40:04.435 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They challenged this narrative
of racial difference.

40:04.469 --> 40:09.774 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so we used the apparatus of
punishment,
the narrative of punishment to
carry out these

40:09.807 --> 40:11.442 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
lynchings.

40:11.476 --> 40:14.445 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And when lynchings were shut
down because
of federal pressure, they moved
indoors.

40:14.479 --> 40:19.217 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we had a criminal justice
system and still
have a criminal justice system
that operates

40:19.250 --> 40:23.921 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
where too often there are
presumptions of
dangerousness and guilt that get
assigned

40:23.955 --> 40:25.990 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to black and brown people.

40:26.024 --> 40:30.495 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The wrongful convictions, the
overincarceration
of people of color, these
disparities in sentencing

40:30.528 --> 40:35.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are rooted in this history of
criminalizing
and demonizing people of color
that is made

40:35.833 --> 40:38.002 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
most dramatic in this era of
lynching.

40:38.036 --> 40:41.572 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think, if we understand
it, we will
